-- Family Dollar May same-store sales up 1.8 pct
-- 
-- Thu Jun 5, 2008 12:26pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/05/us-usa-retailsales-familydollar-idUSN0530532120080605

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Discount retailer Family Dollar Stores Inc ( FDO.N ) reported on Thursday a 1.8 percent increase in May sales at stores open at least a year, double the average Wall Street estimate. 

 Analysts, on average, had been expecting a same-store sales increase of 0.9 percent, according to Thomson Reuters data. The company's own forecast was between flat and up 2 percent. Net sales for the four weeks ended May 31 rose 4.4 percent to $545.0 million. For June, the retailer said it expects same-store sale to rise 2 percent to 4 percent. (Reporting by  Martinne Geller ; editing by John Wallace)